No audio when played back on PS3. Seems related to the fact the audio was ripped in Variable Bit Rate (VBR) format instead of CBR (Continuous Bit Rate). 

I rebuilt the AVI using VideoDub and changed the audio to CBR and now it plays back on the PS3 however, the audio is quite out of synch (I'd estimate about 1 second ahead of the video). Very distracting to watch it that way when you hear the voice and then a second later the lips move :-) ... funny.

Anyone find a good torrent of this properly built to play back on PS3? 

Thanks.

Sorry guys, program is called VirtualDub. I reprocessed the file and added a 1500ms delay to the audio and it runs very nicely on the PS3 now. Give that a try if you are having problems with audio synch.
